                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/math-423" class="program-course-title">
              MATH 423 Regression and Analysis of Variance (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-29546" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Mathematics and Statistics (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/615">Faculty of Science</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Mathematics &amp; Statistics (Sci)              : Least-squares estimators and their properties. Analysis of variance. Linear models with general covariance. Multivariate normal and chi-squared distributions; quadratic forms. General linear hypothesis: F-test and t-test. Prediction and confidence intervals. Transformations and residual plot. Balanced designs.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Fall 2014          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:                        David Stephens (Fall)                  </p>

    
